  "prompt": "What is a boy/girl called when he/she is 1-6 years old, 6-11years old, 11-14 years old, and 14-18 years old?",
  "response": "Here are the common terms used for boys and girls at different age ranges:\n\n1. **1-6 years old**: \n   - **Toddler** (typically 1-3 years)\n   - **Preschooler** (typically 3-5 years)\n\n2. **6-11 years old**: \n   - **Child** or **Middle Childhood**\n   - This stage is often referred to more specifically as **Elementary School Age**.\n\n3. **11-14 years old**: \n   - **Tween** or **Pre-teen**\n   - This age is often considered part of the **Early Adolescence** phase.\n\n4. **14-18 years old**: \n   - **Teenager** or **Adolescent**\n\nThese terms can vary slightly by culture and may have some overlap depending on specific definitions used.",
